Week 1
Linux internals
~1.5 hrs/day
Mon
Processes + PIDs. Read: how Linux process scheduling works. Exercise: trace a Docker container back to its host PID.
90 min
Tue
Namespaces + cgroups. Manually create a namespace with unshare. Find a container's cgroup. Understand K8s resource limits.
90 min
Wed
File descriptors + I/O. Reproduce "too many open files". Understand stdin/stdout/stderr redirection fully.
90 min
Thu
System performance. Use top, vmstat, iostat during a stress test. Diagnose a high-load scenario.
90 min
Fri
Explain day — no new content. Explain this week's concepts to someone or write a short blog post. If you can't explain it, you haven't learned it.
60 min
Weekend
Build: set up a VM (Hetzner CX11 = ₹300/mo). Break things intentionally. Debug from first principles. Read one Julia Evans zine.
2–3 hrs
Week 2
Networking
~1.5 hrs/day
Mon
TCP/IP. Use tcpdump to capture a real handshake. Understand all TCP states. Connection refused vs timeout — know the difference.
90 min
Tue
DNS deep dive. dig +trace every domain you can think of. Debug a broken DNS in a K8s pod. Understand CoreDNS search domains.
90 min
Wed
Subnets + routing. Create two network namespaces, connect with veth pair. Build a mental VPC in your terminal before building in AWS.
90 min
Thu
TLS. Inspect real certificates with openssl. Generate your own CA. Understand what breaks when a cert expires in production.
90 min
Fri
Explain day. Draw the full network stack from application layer to physical. Explain what happens at each layer when you do curl https://google.com.
60 min
Weekend
Build a VPC in AWS by hand — no wizard. Every subnet, route table, security group created manually. Break it and fix it.
2–3 hrs
Week 3
Applied — K8s + AWS debugging
~1.5 hrs/day
Mon
Deploy app on local K8s (kind or minikube). Break it 3 ways. Debug each using only week 1–2 knowledge. No Googling the symptom.
90 min
Tue
K8s networking: add NetworkPolicy, break service-to-service communication, restore it. Explain every rule you write.
90 min
Wed
AWS: deploy the same app on EKS with ALB. Break it with wrong security group. Debug using VPC flow logs + kubectl describe.
90 min
Thu
503 simulation. Kill pods, misconfigure DNS, wrong port. Practice the "10-minute diagnosis" out loud for each failure mode.
90 min
Fri
Final proof test. Sit down, no docs. Answer: explain what happens when a K8s pod can't reach a service. Every hop. Every check. Time yourself.
60 min
Weekend
Write a 1-page incident postmortem for something you broke and fixed this week. This is your interview story.
2 hrs
Resources — free or near-free

Julia Evans zines (jvns.ca) — best Linux + networking writing anywhere. Start with "How DNS Works" and "Networking! ACK!"
"The Linux Command Line" by William Shotts — free online. Read chapters on processes and signals.
Hetzner CX11 or AWS free tier for a practice VM. Break things there, not in your head.
Wireshark — for visualising TCP/TLS handshakes. There's no substitute for seeing real packets.
KillerCoda.com — free K8s playground with networking scenarios already set up.